				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="お前の罪は何色だ！ (Omae no Tsumi ha Naniiro da!)" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#138;&amp;#229;&amp;#137;&amp;#141;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#174;&amp;#231;&amp;#189;&amp;#170;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#175;&amp;#228;&amp;#189;&amp;#149;&amp;#232;&amp;#137;&amp;#178;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#160;&amp;#239;&amp;#188;&amp;#129; (Omae no Tsumi ha Naniiro da!) is a card game from Japan, themed on the Seven Deadly Sins. The sins on the cards are colour coded, giving the game title as What Colour Is Your Sin?.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players are trying to build up colour sets of cards of the Mortal Sins, taking from a tableau or the draw deck, and then pay them down to take the Deadly Sins. When a player has enough Deadly Sins, they win.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;But the Mortal and Deadly Sin cards also carry special effects, which make life easier for the player, or harder for the other players. For example, Gluttony or Greed let players draw more cards. Securing the Deadly Sin card Pride means the other players cannot draw from the deck, forcing them to take cards they don't want from the tableau. The sin Wrath reduces their hand limit from 7 to 6 cards.&amp;#10;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
